<item>
            <title>[DERBY-198] Add Support for network Server USRIDONL security</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-198</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently Network Server supports only two security mechanisms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;User ID and password  (usridpwd)&lt;br/&gt;
User ID and encrypted password (eusridpwd)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It would be good to add support for  User ID Only security so that it could more closely match the embedded driver and not always require a password.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See details of security mechanism implementations in section 4.4.2.1 of &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DRDA V3 Vol. 1: Distributed Relational Database Architecture &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.opengroup.org/dbiop/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.opengroup.org/dbiop/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
